chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you’ve used illegal drugs or misused prescription drugs.
chunks.plain_content:
Drug use and driving
You must tell DVLA if you’ve used illegal drugs or misused prescription drugs.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You can be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Drug use and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You can be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
Fill in form DG1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.

In Northern Ireland you must tell the DVA. Fill in form DL1.
